\com The phonological form of this word is /VhṼʔ/. The tongue height and the degree of labial closure and in the segment before and after [h] vary; [ʌ] and [u] are the endpoints of a continuum. A full closure ([ʔmhm]) is possible as well (but never transcribed?). [h] can be dropped in fast speech.
