\alt aʔho
\alt oho
\alt ohoho
\alt ohoi
\alt okho
\alt okhokho
\alt oʔkhou
\alt okkhou
\alt okhou
\alt ou
\alt oʔho
\alt oʔhoi
\alt oʔhou
\ps interj
\de oh
\seme exclamation of surprise
\gn अहो
\lg N
\com The phonological form of this word is /VkhV/. Both vowels are low and vary between [ʌ] and [o], [ʌho] being the most typical realisation. The second vowel should be equal to or higher than the first, so [ohʌ] is impossible. [i] or [u] are frequently added to the second vowel to reinforce the rising movement. The consonant in the middle has the usual free variants [kʰ], [x], [h], but also appears geminated as [kːʰ]. 
\qst

