\lex jhil
\ct jhĩma
\morph jhĩ
\morph jhin
\ps vi
\val S-NOM(1) V-s(S)
\de be.peeled; peel.off
\gn च्याटिनु
\lg C
\qst there is some confusion around the stems jhil- 'peel', jhɨl- 'ruffle' and jhɨs- 'bare'. One informant said that 'peel' should be jhɨs-. Other informants said that jhil-, jhɨl- and jhɨs- all three mean the same, namely 'ruffle' or 'bare'. The present meanings are constructed from what was found in the community dictionary and from a few corpus instances.

