\gns बिश्वास गर्नु; पत्याउनु; टेर्नु
\ex Akka hana apatte kaʔnaʔã.
\exe I believe you.
\exn म तिमीलाई पत्याउँछु ।
\exsrc field notes ROS
\se pepma kaiʔma
\des feel.sick
\gn उल्टी हुनु
\se ramma kaiʔma
\des be.happy.about; be.pleased.at; like
\gns मन पराउनु; खुशी लाग्नु
\se rek kaiʔma
\des get.angry.with
\gns रिसाउनु
\se remsu kaiʔma
\des envy; be.jealous.of
\gns ईर्ष्या गर्नु
\ex Huĩsaŋa jogoce yaŋ uremsu kattukuce.
\exe He's jealous of everyone.
\exn उसले जुनैलाई पनि ईर्ष्या गर्छ ।
\exsrc field notes ROS
\com Example VAL013 is far from ideal for illustrating the agreement pattern of the associated frame since the two third persons singular implied by the verb suffixes could be linked to any two of the three roles (experiencer, stimulus, emotion). We have examples for other verbs from this class where linking is unambiguous.
\qst

