\lex -khag
\morph -khaw
\morph -kha
\morph -kh
\ps v2
\de CON
\seme try doing something, do something and see what happens. Reinforces imperatives and similar expressions by emphasising the personal effort the listener is to make
\gn गरिहेर; त
\lg C
\ex Nunucenɨŋ khela numdakhanĩ naŋ.
\exe Come on, play with the babies.
\exn नानीहरूसँग खेल त ।
\exsrc Ch4R12S08 230
\com -khaŋ and its regular allomorphs occur outside the imperative, -kha and prevocalic -kh inside. -kha with imperatives truncates the second IMP -a and in this way lets surface vowels otherwise dropped before -a.
\qst

