\lex -lond
\morph -lon
\morph -loĩ
\ps v2
\de out
\gn
\lg C
\com -lond can only be distinguished from -loĩs before a vowel - before consonants and at the end of words the two have exactly the same allomorphs. However, since -loĩs is much more frequent than -lond in the non-ambiguous context, -loĩs should also be the default in the ambiguous context. Only choose -lond when the morphophonology allows no other choice. The difference between the form is not clear yet; transitivity agreement can be excluded because -loĩs can be used with V1 of all valencies. 
\qst

