\lex -na
\ps gm
\de NEG
\gn -न
\lg N
\reg Eastern Nepali
\com Whereas in standard Nepali old -do [NPST.PTCP] non.past.participle appears fused with -ʌi [EMPH] and -nʌ [NEG] in NPST.NEG (e.g. jã-dʌin-ʌũ [go-NEG-1p] < *-do-ʌi-nʌ-ʌm), -ʌi is not used in the east and agreement suffixes intervene between -do and the negation so that it becomes segmentable (e.g. jã-d-um-nʌ [go-NEG-1p-NEG] < *-do-ʌm-nʌ). 
\qst

